description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a band 8A matron within the directorate of Surgery and Trauma and Orthopaedics. This is a time of unprecedented change within the NHS, with our Trust redesigning both its emergency and elective surgical pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be joining a very strong senior nursing team and will be providing Matron cover for both surgical inpatients services on the Ealing Site and line managing orthopaedic specialist nurses across 2 sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced registered nurse who has experience of leading a team. This person must have good leadership skills and have the ability to be able to prioritise at short notice their workload, the matron role sits between being operational and being a clinical lead and therefore the post holder will be providing professional clinical and managerial leadership to nursing and associated staff. The Matrons role is pivotal to ensuring the provision of a high quality responsive nursing service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also undertake the key functions of the matron role ensuring the attainment and monitoring of quality and clinical performance indicators and ensuring that any aspect of Directorate service delivery is underpinned by the patient and service user experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Ruth Cross&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:Head of Nursing - Surgical Specialities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: ruth.cross@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07771982854&lt;/p&gt;
